               <head>Haft Qulzum, letter pa</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Haft qulzum</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007002370" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3715-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Persian dictionary and grammar created at the order of the Nāʾib-Navvāb Ghāzī al-Dīn Ḥaydar, later King of Avadh (Oudh)</p>
                        <p>Fascicule consists of the section on pāʾ, that is the third baḥr from the first qulzum</p>
                        <p>Clear nastaʿlīq with lemata repeated in margins in red naskh (vide printed edition, Lakhnaʾu 1237/1822)</p>
                        <p>European wattermarked papers: WP 1819</p>
                        <p>Illuminated sarlawḥ added later</p>
                        <p>Dated Avadh royal seals in red vermilion or āl/shangarf ink: Amjad ʿAli Shah and Vajid ʿAli Shah</p>
                        <p>Dated: third volume completed by ʿAbd al-Ḥamīd the royal servant, 11 Shaʿbān 1241/21 March 1826</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21823">Haft qulzum</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21823">هفت قلزم</title>
                  </msItem>
